Complete frontend (React + Tailwind + Axios + Context API)

Complete backend (Node + Express + MongoDB)

Folder structure:

ecommerce-app/
├── backend/
│   ├── server.js
│   ├── config/db.js
│   ├── models/productModel.js
│   ├── routes/productRoutes.js
│   ├── controllers/productController.js
│   └── data/products.js
└── frontend/
    ├── src/
    │   ├── App.js
    │   ├── index.js
    │   ├── context/CartContext.js
    │   ├── components/
    │   │   ├── Navbar.js
    │   │   ├── ProductCard.js
    │   │   ├── ProductDetails.js
    │   │   └── Cart.js
    │   ├── pages/
    │   │   ├── Home.js
    │   │   └── NotFound.js
    │   └── styles/App.css

Backend Codebase (ecommerce-app/backend):
server.js - Main entry point with Express.js setup
config/db.js - Database connection configuration
models/productModel.js - Product schema definition
routes/productRoutes.js - API route definitions
controllers/productController.js - Request handlers
data/products.js - Sample product data
seeder.js - Data seeding script

Frontend Codebase (ecommerce-app/frontend):
src/App.js - Main application component
src/index.js - Entry point
src/context/CartContext.js - Cart state management
src/components/Navbar.js - Navigation bar
src/components/ProductCard.js - Product display component
src/components/ProductDetails.js - Product detail view
src/components/Cart.js - Shopping cart
src/pages/Home.js - Homepage
src/pages/NotFound.js - 404 page

The project is already fully implemented with:
RESTful API for product management
React frontend with responsive UI
Cart functionality with persistent state
MongoDB integration
Proper routing and error handling

